      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So if the noise is \"structured,\" it means something specific is causing certain data points to deviate in a way that isn't just random chance? Like, if I saw a pattern in the residuals that looked intentional or weirdly consistent, how would I actually describe that in a formal paper? I don't want to sound like I'm just making things up to explain away my bad p-value.",
