      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If your residuals show a pattern, it strongly suggests that your model is missing a key explanatory variable, which is a much more rigorous finding than simply \"noise.\" You can formally describe this by conducting diagnostic checks on your model assumptions, such as plotting residuals against fitted values or time. If a pattern emerges, you should state that the assumption of independent and identically distributed errors is violated, and the pattern itself needs to be identified as potential systematic bias. This moves the discussion from statistical failure to a methodological critique of your current model.",
      "source": "target",
